        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer79736598" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer14687439195691842241"><br/><br/><br/><br/>A very good and interesting account of a group of men from A Company, 116th Infantry Regiment, 29th Infantry Division, who were part of the first wave at Omaha Beach in 1944. I found the book easy to read and captivating, following these men from enlistment and training to the beaches at Normandy. A deeply touching book about a bunch of normal people from the small town of Bedford and what happened to them and their families, highly recommended.</span>

          </span>
        </div>


