<span id="freeTextContainer10981788181153277273"><b>4 Stars</b> for a somber, hard hitting story about one of the first units to hit Omaha beach on D-Day. If you have seen &quot;Saving Private Ryan&quot;, you will get an idea of what they met at the water&apos;s edge. To read about the men and their families, before, during and after brought it so close to home. I recently drove by Bedford, VA but didn&apos;t want to stop until I read this book. I&apos;ll be back that way again soon and will stop to really appreciate the National D-Day Memorial. </span>
